Henry Croxford (14 June 1845 – 15 December 1892) was an English professional cricketer who played for Kent County Cricket Club.
Croxford was born at Hadlow in Kent in 1845. He made his first-class cricket debut for Kent in 1869 before going on to play 27 times for the county. He made his final first-class appearance for Kent in 1877. During the 1873 season he made an appearance for a team of professionals employed at Prince's Cricket Ground in Chelsea, London.Croxford died at Faversham in 1892 aged 47.
